  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>

    <h3>Landmark Navigation</h3>
    <p>The <code>&lt;search&gt;</code> element is a landmark, meaning screen reader users can jump directly to it using landmark navigation. This replaces the older pattern of <code>&lt;form role="search"&gt;</code>.</p>

    <h3>Labeling</h3>
    <p>Always provide a label for the search input. Options include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Visible <code>&lt;label&gt;</code> element</li>
      <li>Visually hidden <code>&lt;label&gt;</code> using <code>.visually-hidden</code></li>
      <li><code>aria-label</code> attribute on the input</li>
    </ul>

    <code-block language="html">{{ labelingExamplesCode | safe }}</code-block>

    <h3>input[type="search"] vs input[type="text"]</h3>
    <p>Always use <code>type="search"</code> for search inputs. It provides:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Clear button in some browsers</li>
      <li>Appropriate keyboard on mobile (search button instead of enter)</li>
      <li>Semantic meaning for assistive technologies</li>
      <li>Search-specific styling opportunities</li>
    </ul>

